<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1003]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[487,570,258,283]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
) with pattern similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[932,1054,259,283]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krameri">
<emphasis box="[932,1054,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. krameri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1304,258,283]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 92</figureCitation>
) with three large anterior yellow marks and one posterior mark, bordered by dark brown. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1322,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Figs 92, 93</figureCitation>
) red with numerous small bluish-white maculae on clavus and adjacent corium; outer discal cell with irregular white stripe adjacent to outer margin; apical portion gray. Face (
<figureCitation box="[726,806,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
) with pattern similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[1152,1271,366,390]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krameri">
<emphasis box="[1152,1271,366,390]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. krameri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male pygofer with long inner ventroapical process, extending medially and crossing median line (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1150,1424,402,427]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="p">Young 1977, fig. 761p</bibRefCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with unpaired ventral process with apical third bifurcated (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[988,1244,438,463]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="f">Young 1977, fig. 761f</bibRefCitation>
). Female sternite VII with broad, subrectangular posteromedian emargination, bordered by short projections. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Figs 95, 96</figureCitation>
) with short, arch-shaped sclerotized plate, broadly concave on anteromedian portion and with broad, median longitudinal depression.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1003]" box="[199,562,582,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
Female length. 
<quantity box="[372,472,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.08" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" unit="mm" value="10.8">10.8 mm</quantity>
(n = 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,258,1003]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,571,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[913,993,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stali">
<emphasis box="[913,993,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. stali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sternite VIII, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
), with short, arch-shaped sclerotized plate; anterior margin of plate broadly convex, with broad and deep median concavity; posterior margin slightly produced and truncate medially; dorsal surface with broad and deep longitudinal median depression; anterior surface (
<figureCitation box="[715,797,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) strongly bilobate dorsolaterally. Pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[185,309,763,786]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[185,309,763,786]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula I, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[648,735,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
), with basal portion slightly broad and bearing short lateral prominence; basal margin slightly oblique, irregular and subtruncate; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1191,1311,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1191,1311,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[353,466,835,858]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[353,466,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A.angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth, on median portion of blade, very prominent, 1.5 to 2 times longer than high, spaced from one another about one tooth length; preapical prominence approximately aligned to tooth anterior to anteapical one.
</paragraph>
